rows.content:
Touchscreen Freeze Issue on Samsung Galaxy F14 5G After 1 November 2024 Update_x000D_
_x000D_
Problem Summary:_x000D_
After updating to the 1 November 2024 security patch on 4 January 2025, my phone's touchscreen started freezing. The touch worked for about 1 minute after every reboot but stopped responding completely after that._x000D_
_x000D_
Steps Taken:_x000D_
_x000D_
1. Rebooted the phone using Power + Volume Down. Touch worked briefly but froze again._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
2. Checked Double Tap to Wake—it worked, suggesting hardware was intact._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
3. Used an OTG mouse to reset all settings, but the issue persisted._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
4. Performed a factory reset, which resolved the issue._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Possible Cause:_x000D_
The problem likely stemmed from a bug in the update, causing a software glitch or corrupted firmware._x000D_
_x000D_
Resolution:_x000D_
A factory reset fixed the issue, and the touchscreen is now functioning normally._x000D_
_x000D_
Suggestion:_x000D_
Please investigate the 1 November 2024 update for potential touchscreen-related bugs and release a patch if necessary._x000D_
rows.Remarks: The touchscreen on the device freezes after a software update, functioning only for a brief period after each reboot before completely stopping response, and the issue is resolved only through a factory reset.

Subject: Request for Dual 5G Support on Samsung Galaxy A53 5G_x000D_
_x000D_
Dear Samsung Support Team,_x000D_
_x000D_
I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to express a concern regarding the Samsung Galaxy A53 5G model. When both SIM slots are in use, only one slot is capable of 5G connectivity, while the other is limited to a maximum of 4G._x000D_

I kindly request Samsung to address this issue and consider implementing dual 5G support on the Galaxy A53 5G through a software update if feasible. _x000D_

_x000D_
Best regards,_x000D_
Md Amirul Islam_x000D_

rows.content:
Hey, _x000D_
This feedback is to help you better your remote help function. _x000D_
_x000D_
Yesterday I contacted remote help to help clear a bug I was facing and they couldn't help me. And I myself fixed it today. _x000D_
_x000D_
The issue was regarding my text fond. While i am on dark mode, my text was having a white border around it. I contacted them to remove this border, and they tried their best and even reset all settings but still the issue persisted. They gave up. _x000D_
_x000D_
So I though why not try some settings myself. And I found it out. Turn out I somehow clicked on 'High Contrast Fonts' some time ago on notification bar and that was the issue. When I switched it off the font went back to normal. _x000D_
_x000D_
So, this feedback is to give you a tip which might help others in the future. When facing with text fond issue, check notification bar and look for high contrast font as well. _x000D_
_x000D_
Thank you. _x000D_
rows.Remarks: The user experienced a white border around text when using dark mode, which was caused by the 'High Contrast Fonts' setting being enabled in the notification bar. Disabling this setting resolved the issue.

Subject: Samsung Galaxy A55 5G Camera Video & Photo Quality Issue_x000D_
_x000D_
Respected Team,_x000D_
_x000D_
I recently purchased the Samsung Galaxy A55 5G, expecting a high-quality camera performance, especially for photography and videography related to architecture. However, I am highly disappointed with the camera quality._x000D_
_x000D_
Issues Observed:_x000D_
_x000D_
1. Lack of Detail & Sharpness – The camera fails to capture architectural details properly, making images look soft and unclear._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
2. Distortion & Noise – The edges of buildings and structures often appear distorted, and noise is visible even in well-lit conditions._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
3. Poor Dynamic Range – The highlights often get overexposed, and shadows lack proper details._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
4. Video Quality Issues – The recorded videos lack stability, sharpness, and color accuracy, making them unsuitable for professional use._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
5. Overprocessing & Artificial Colors – The camera adds excessive processing, making the images look unnatural._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
rows.Remarks: The camera fails to capture architectural details with sufficient sharpness and clarity, showing distortion, noise, poor dynamic range, and unnatural color processing in both photos and videos.

rows.content:
I'm writing to highlight critical areas where the A55's camera image processing needs significant upgrades:_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Camera Processing Concerns_x000D_
- Image processing currently produces artifacts and inconsistent quality, especially in challenging lighting conditions_x000D_
- Noticeable issues with noise in homogeneous areas like sky and indoor shots_x000D_
- Bokeh mode suffers from subject segmentation errors_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Specific Improvement Recommendations_x000D_
1. Enhanced Image Processing_x000D_
- Implement more advanced computational photography techniques_x000D_
- Reduce noise and artifacts in low-light and complex scenes_x000D_
- Improve color accuracy and dynamic range_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
2. Video Stabilization_x000D_
- Upgrade electronic image stabilization (EIS) to match top-tier devices_x000D_
- Reduce video cropping, especially in front camera mode_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
3. Zoom Quality_x000D_
- Address subpar 2x zoom performance with better digital zoom processing_x000D_
- Consider adding computational zoom capabilities similar to flagship models_x000D_
rows.Remarks: The user reports that the A55's camera image processing produces artifacts and inconsistent quality, especially in low light and complex lighting conditions, with issues in noise reduction, sky and indoor shots, and subject segmentation in bokeh mode. The user also requests improvements in video stabilization and zoom quality.

rows.content:
Subject: Feature Suggestion for Auto Step Detection in Samsung Health_x000D_
_x000D_
Dear Samsung Team,_x000D_
_x000D_
I am Shivansh from India, a Computer Science student, and a long-time user of the Samsung Health app. I appreciate the functionality it provides, but I have noticed an issue that affects step count accuracy._x000D_
_x000D_
Currently, when traveling in a bus, the app continues counting steps unless manually paused, leading to inaccurate data. I propose an automatic step detection feature that uses distance/time calculations along with the user's height, weight, and average human walking speed to determine if the movement is physically possible. This would help differentiate actual steps from vehicle motion and improve accuracy without requiring manual intervention._x000D_
_x000D_
I believe this feature would enhance the user experience and make Samsung Health even more reliable. I would love to see this considered for future updates._x000D_
_x000D_
Thank you for your time._x000D_
_x000D_
Best regards,_x000D_
Shivansh_x000D_
India_x000D_
_x000D_
rows.Remarks: The user suggests adding an automatic step detection feature in Samsung Health to distinguish between actual walking and vehicle motion, improving step count accuracy without requiring manual intervention.

rows.content: When the charger is plugged in, super fast charging mode is shown instantly, but within a few seconds, it shifts to only charging mode. This is happening after the October security patch 2024. Now my A55 is running on the latest software security patch of January 2025. I first thought, if my adapter is problematic. But it's not. I changed my Samsung adapter, and bought the same 25W official Samsung adapter again to be clarified. Still, the A55 is charging in only charging mode. But in battery settings, it shows, super fast charger is connected. But after so many results, I observed that the phone is charging slower than it should charge according to its power delivery. No doubt, it's a software issue. Samsung should pay heed to this issue of A55 battery charging seriously. Slow charging is too outdated and time killing in 2025. Subject: Charging Issue on Samsung Galaxy A55 5G_x000D_
_x000D_
Dear Samsung Support Team,_x000D_
_x000D_

rows.content:
Mera Samsung device galaxy m34 BGMI (Battlegrounds Mobile India) game khelte time **bahut jyada heat karta hai**, aur saath hi **FPS (Frame Rate) bhi kafi gir jata hai**. Ye issue pehle thand ke season mein manageable tha, lekin ab garmi ke season mein bahut badh gaya hai. Device ka temperature itna high ho jata hai ki game khelna almost impossible ho jata hai, aur FPS drop ke karan gameplay experience completely kharab ho jata hai.  1. **Heating Issue:** Device abnormally heat karta hai, especially BGMI khelte time.  _x000D_
2. **FPS Drop:** Jab device heat karta hai, FPS drastically gir jata hai, jisse game laggy aur unplayable ho jata hai. _x000D_
3. **Already Optimized:** Main already sab kuch try kar chuka hoon: _x000D_
 - Background apps close kiye hain. _x000D_
 - Device ka cache clear kiya hai. _x000D_
 - Game Booster settings optimize kiye hain. _x000D_
 - Software updated hai. _x000D_
 - Device ko cool environment mein use kiya hai. _x000D_
 - Power-saving mode off rakha hai. _x000D_
4. **No Improvement:** In sab ke baawjood, issue abhi _x000D_
rows.Remarks: The device overheats significantly during gameplay in the BGMI app, leading to a sharp drop in FPS and making gameplay laggy and unplayable, despite the user having tried all common troubleshooting steps including closing background apps, clearing cache, optimizing game booster settings, and ensuring software updates.

rows.content:
My old Samsung A 21 S has supported me well past 4 yrs which had 3.5mm TRRS Audio Jack._x000D_
This was supporting all my requirements not only for voice calls, Audio video calls on whatsapp and for my external applications i use like Smule karaoke App and for going Live in Social media including Facebook live for my Live singing sessionss._x000D_
Recently i have bought a new Samsung Mobile Galaxy F55 model, which is USB c type for Both Chatting and for Head phones._x000D_
While the Audio quality on replay is working fine, the Mic quality on even a ordy Voice recorder is Bad._x000D_
When i go on Live with A21s model, i used to give a TRRS connection to Audio port from my Analogue mixer Line out through an Interface like I rig._x000D_
When i tried the same connection to get converted to USB C type through an adapter of 3.5 mm TRRS female to USB c type Male to get Connetted to my New Samsung Mobile F 55 model. The audio recording quality is totally distorted._x000D_
rows.Remarks: The microphone quality on the new Galaxy F55 model is poor, resulting in distorted audio recordings even during simple voice recording, and the audio quality degrades when using a TRRS audio connection via an adapter from an external analog mixer.

rows.content:
This is about using this device for going Live on social media, when an analogue audio from a mixer via an interface which has 3.5 mm trrs male out put is given to this F55 model mobile USB C via a USB c male to 3.5 mm female adapter both passive or active, the voice gets distorted, earlier with A 21 s model with 3.5 mm dedicated Slot for headphones is working fine, the Audio on live with any social media is perfect. But when the same connection gets converted to a USB C through an adapter the voice gets distorted. So this USB C type on F 55 model is not supporting the Audio signal from a Mixer routed through an Interface like I Rig whereas the same is going well with A 21 S dedicated 3.5 mm port. _x000D_
I have tried both passive adapters and active adapters with Live DAC inbuilt. Its not working as it works with A 21 S model. _x000D_
Need some Technical support who can technically understand the requirement and attend this query.  _x000D_
rows.Remarks: The audio signal from a mixer, routed through an interface and connected via a USB-C adapter, results in distortion when used for live streaming on the Galaxy F55, while the same setup works perfectly on the Galaxy A21S with its dedicated 3.5 mm headphone port.
